        <svcproc svcproctype="align" graphiccount="0">
            <title>VERIFY AIR CONDITIONING COMPRESSOR PULLEY ALIGNMENT</title>
            <para>The refrigerant compressor pulley must be aligned with the fan drive pulley. A slight adjustment of
                the compressor in the mounting bracket will accomplish this alignment.
            </para>
        </svcproc>
        <svcproc svcproctype="check" graphiccount="0">
            <title>VERIFY THE PRESENCE OF A BACK SIDE IDLER</title>
            <para>Refer to Items 2, 3, 4, 5 and 6,
                <hotlnk xrefid="f9412021">Figure 1</hotlnk>
            </para>
            <para>Vehicles built after December, 1991, will have this idler pulley. If the engine is not equipped with
                an idler pulley, it must be installed. Refer to
                <hotlnk xrefid="t9412021">back side idler parts list.</hotlnk>
            </para>
        </svcproc>
        <svcproc svcproctype="check" graphiccount="0">
            <title>VERIFY THE PRESENCE OF A NYLON FAN</title>
            <para>Vehicles built after February 1, 1993, will have a nylon fan. If the engine has a steel fan, it must
                be replaced with a nylon fan.
            </para>
            <para>When installing the new nylon fan, install a spacer with the fan to be sure the fan blades do not come
                in contact with the crankshaft damper or protrusions on the front of the engine.
            </para>
            <para>Locate the correct combination of fan, spacer and mounting bolts in the parts catalog for the model
                year being serviced.
            </para>
        </svcproc>
        <svcproc svcproctype="check" graphiccount="1">
            <title>VERIFY THE PRESENCE OF A REFRIGERANT COMPRESSOR PULLEY WITH "SIDEBOARDS"</title>
            <para>Refer to
                <hotlnk xrefid="f9412022">Figure 2</hotlnk>
            </para>
            <para>Vehicles built after July 28, 1993, will have a compressor pulley with "sideboards"
                <hotlnk xrefid="f9412022">Figure 2.</hotlnk>If the compressor has the old style pulley, it must be
                replaced.
            </para>
            <figure id="f9412022" figsize="pg-wide">
                <graphic filename="../tsifigures/G9412022.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 2. Pulley With Sideboards</caption>
            </figure>
        </svcproc>
        <svcproc svcproctype="check" graphiccount="0">
            <title>VERIFY THAT THE AIR CONDITIONING SYSTEM REFRIGERANT CHARGE IS WITHIN SPECIFICATIONS</title>
            <para>Overcharge of the system can contribute to flipping the belt off. Refrigerant specifications are
                listed in CTS-5070 in GROUP 16 of the CTS-5000 Master Service Manual.
            </para>
        </svcproc>
        <svcproc svcproctype="replace" graphiccount="0">
            <title>REPLACE PULLEY ON THE REFRIGERANT COMPRESSOR BELT TENSIONER</title>
            <para>The correct pulley for this fix is 1-1/2 inches (39 mm) wide with a flanged edge/sideboard (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f9412022">Figure 2</hotlnk>). The pulley presently on the belt tensioner will be 1-1/4
                or 1-1/2 inches wide with a smooth non-flanged surface. Replace this with the 1-1/2 inch (39 mm) wide
                pulley with flanged/sideboards (Part No. 2028957C2).
                <emph type="bold">DO NOT REUSE THE WASHER/DUST COVER REMOVED WITH THE OLD (SMOOTH SIDE) PULLEY.</emph>If
                the washer/dust cover is installed on the bolt with the new pulley, the new pulley will be bound up and
                will not rotate. Tighten the bolt and install dust cap (Part No. 1820566C1).
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <important>
                    <para>Install new refrigerant compressor belt if old belt is damaged or worn.</para>
                </important>
            </specpara>
            <para>Belt Part Number 1687799C1</para>
        </svcproc>
